  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-15.2B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+21.0B), dealers are likely flat to slightly buying the dip as spot hovers near support. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX concentration at 6605-6610 creates a strong magnet effect above current levels, while the negative gamma floor at 6590 provides amplified buying support if we test lower. The gex_surge event combined with the -24% to -52% recent GEX changes suggests dealers are actively rebalancing hedges, creating choppy action as flows stabilize around these key strikes.\n\nKey levels: 6590 (dealer buying accelerates below), 6605 (heavy dealer selling above), and 6627 flip strike where regime shifts.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6605 with support building above 6590.",
